{
  "doc_id": "1603",
  "text": "Fortunately, with the development of psycho-linguistic and text mining analysis methods, there are multiple computational methods to model people's personality from their digital footprints. The seminal works from Golbeck et al. use psycholinguistic analysis to model Big 5 personality from Twitter [CITATION_1] . Holtgraves found correlations between Linguistic Inquiry and Word Count (LIWC) categories in users' text messages and their personality traits [CITATION_2] . Yarkoni also found significant correlation among Big 5 personality and LIWC with blog data [CITATION_3] . Mairesse et.al illustrated the usefulness of different algorithms for automatic recognition of personal-ity traits both in conversation and text [CITATION_4] . Gou el.al studied feasibility and effectiveness of modeling users' personality traits with online social media contents [CITATION_5] .",
